Reflecting, perhaps, at this point that when Alexander had no more worlds to conquer he then began to complain, Dante proceeds to argue that this Monarchy, far from passing into despotism, is itself the fulfilment and safeguard os liberty. {grue liberty does not mean an equal exposure to good an to evil, but con- firmation in the way of goodness.
